I had a question about implementing the `tower_http::follow_redirect::Policy`. 

I used `FollowRedirect<HyperClient, TowerPolicy>` as a `hyper` filed,  and called it in the `loop`. This will make the `TowerPolicy<B, E>` meets `E = hyper_util::client::legacy::Error`.  That's say B will be `async_impl::body::Body`, E will be `hyper_util::client::legacy::Error`.

My questions is how convert ActionKind::Error into `hyper_util::client::legacy::Error` ?

<details>

<summary> implemention of tower_http::follow_redirect::Policy </summary>

```
impl TowerPolicy<async_impl::body::Body, hyper_util::client::legacy::Error>
    for TowerRedirectPolicy
{
    fn redirect(
        &mut self,
        attempt: &TowerAttempt<'_>,
    ) -> std::result::Result<
        tower_http::follow_redirect::policy::Action,
        hyper_util::client::legacy::Error,
    > {
        let previous = attempt.previous();
        let next = attempt.location();
        let next_url = Url::parse(&attempt.location().to_string()).unwrap();
        let previous_url = Url::parse(&attempt.previous().to_string()).unwrap();
        match self
            .policy
            .check(attempt.status(), &next_url, &[previous_url])
        {
            ActionKind::Follow => Ok(TowerAction::Follow),
            ActionKind::Stop => Ok(TowerAction::Stop),
           // The policy err can't convert into `hyper_util::client::legacy::Error`
            ActionKind::Error(err) => Err(hyper_util::client::legacy::Error),
        }
    }

}
```

